<br>
Friendship.  The guild members can count on me to drop out of a existing pick-up group to do them a favor.  It should not become a nusance though.  I maintain contact through the day via AIM and email and generally respond promptly.  I participate on the message boards.<br>
<br>
Role play.  Light to moderate RP desired.  I don't want to read 3 page posts in troll or dwarf (I hit dem guud... etc), and like to get to know the people behind the character as well.  I enjoy the RP aspect very much, but am by no means a nazi about it.<br>
<br>
Allignment - I PREFER good or neutral alligned guilds.  I have a lighthearded and fun personality and find it very difficult to be mean.  I will not rule out neutral/evil guilds if they have everything else.<br>
<br>
Leadership - Strong leadership.  The councils and &quot;everyone has a vote&quot; leadership styles have not shown themselves to be very effective to me.  They can't be going through a leadership transition or have gone through one in the last 3 months.<br>
<br>
Mature - Name calling, and generally immature behavior is (dewd-speak) is right out for me.  If I have a conflict with someone I handle it in a mature and level-headed way.<br>
<br>
Technology - The group should use a raid calendar, have a decent sized message board, and have a fair method for distributing loot on raids.<br>
<br>
Does anything like this exist?<br>
 <p>Zapoo the Wise<BR>
